<br>
1)East Karana - Felonius Sworddancer - at base of ramp to High Hold - hail to start quest, ask to hear story about ogres (I believe you can skip this step.)<br>
2)East Freeport - Kargek Redblade - dwarf near SK &amp; Rogue guild - talk to him, he gives you a letter<br>
3)Feerrott - Oknoggin Stonemasher - near a bridge - give him letter, he gives you a tiny lute<br>
4)East Freeport - Kargek - give him tiny lute, he gives you a book<br>
5)East Karana - Tenal Redblade - at end of path below HH ramp - give him book, he gives you Freezing Water Totem, wants you to bring totem back along with Heart of Ice<br>
A)Permafrost - Goblin Wizard - kill and loot Heart of Ice<br>
Give Tenal Freezing Water Totem and Heart of Ice, he gives you Totem of Raging War, wants you to bring totem back with Red and Green Scales of the Children of Veeshan (dragons)<br>
B)Emerald Jungle - Severilous - kill and loot Green Scales<br>
Ok...since there is NO reliable info I could find on how Severilious spawns, and when you can get him, decided to post here. (some added info i fould on the web on serv)<br>
<br>
So your a warrior, your 60, you want your epic, and you know you have enough friends or a guild who will help you as SOON as sev pops, heres what to do. <br>
<br>
First, if you want to start out on a clean slate for him, get a druid/ranger around level 35+ to EJ before a patch. <br>
<br>
When patch is over, move your tracker to FoB zone, from there, follow the wall so that its on your left, and follow it till you get to FOUR pillars in a strait line heading to the side of a cliff. <br>
<br>
That is the camp spot, park your tracker on the wall there, (not the cliff wall) and that is your new home for the next 4 days. <br>
<br>
From what I gathered on his spawn time, he can spawn 1-3 days after a patch, when he spawns you will see him on track there. <br>
<br>
You need to keep the tracker there 24/7 checking on him. <br>
<br>
things you should know about him : <br>
1) He is gimp, 3 groups of level 60 people can own him with 0 deaths, easily. <br>
2) He does NOT always drop the green scale, but he can drop up to 2. He dropped none when I camped him :( <br>
3) He has 2 AE's, Fear and Stun, Fear you can get past by using Bark Potions, Stun I resisted every time with 200+ SV poison. <br>
4) He is level 60, so will show up just like the name of a player if your tracker is level 60. You can also see his pet up on track. Being 60 means if you are level 60 when you fight him, easy resists. <br>
5) He runs faster then sow. You need a bard with Selo's to pull him, or someone with Scale of Wolf would probobly work also...be careful though if he stuns you your screwed. <br>
6) He only has 32k hps, once again, VERY easy kill. <br>
7) Only hard part about him really, would be first, camping him. Second, getting your guild/friends mobolized in EJ before others find out hes up, and maybe the pull if you don't have capable people <br>
<br>
C)Skyfire or Timorous Deep - Talendor or Faydedar - kill and loot Red Scales<br>
Give Tenal Totem of Raging War, Red and Green Scales, he gives you Mark of the Sword, wants you to bring him Mark of the Sword and Arm of Maestro<br>
D)Plane of Hate - Maestro of Rancor - kill and loot Arm of Maestro<br>
Give Tenal Mark of the Sword and Arm of Maestro, he gives you Note to Kargek<br>
6)Plane of Sky - Spiroc Lord - kill and loot Spiroc Wingblade<br>
7)East Freeport - Kargek - give him Note to Kargek and Spiroc Wingblade, he gives you Red Scabbard and instructions to combine in it the Ancient Blade, Ancient Sword Blade, Finely Crafted Dragon Head Hilt and Jeweled Dragon Head Hilt to receive your reward.<br>
8)Lake Rathetear - Unjeweled Dragon Hilt - loc pos 2797, pos 81 - in bag at bottom of lake<br>
